column12: A canal, is it? Fascinating. If we had a ferry, we could put these days of endlessly running about behind us.
Don't you just float everywhere anyway?
Do you think I am borne aloft by the winds, lad? It takes stamina to maintain this height!
Oh... Really?
You could at least try to hide the utter dismay, you know...
I'm willing to bet that man knows more about his wife absconding than he is letting on...
Yeah, I'm curious, too—but for now, we should just focus on finding her.
If she has truly left this charming hamlet, finding her may prove most difficult indeed.
I just hope she hasn't been attacked by Shades or anything...
Hmm... Something about that Shade seems rather...odd.
I cannot imagine the woman with the red bag would have ventured this far.
Perhaps our time would be best spent focusing on a search of the southern plains.
That Shade dropped something. We had best return to claim it.
Heavens, that was exhausting...
Tell me about it. Anyway, let's go give Popola an update.
The couple with the red bags were a strange pair indeed.
It boggles the mind to think their relationship can persist despite such intense squabbling.
Well, they looked pretty happy in the end, at least.
Maybe the secret to living a happy life is sharing your feelings even when they're sorta mean and weird.
If you adopt such a strategy, I may leave for groceries one day and never return...
How excellent to know the canal is finished! Hopefully this puts our days of running all over behind us.
The faster we can move, the faster we can save Yonah.
Let's use it as often as we need.
This feels alarmingly familiar.
Pah! I'm sure that couple is merely having another one of their inane spats.
Let us do our utmost not to get dragged into it this time, mmm?
And here we go again! *sigh* Shall we begin by asking around at the tavern like before?
To think that couple's petty squabbles have become something of an attraction for the locals...
Doesn't surprise me in the least.
Seeing people like that puts a little spring in your step, you know?
You humans truly are a maddening bunch. Such buffoonery does little more than wear this old tome out!
We searched the southern plains back when the wife ran off, too, right?
I believe we did, yes.
A lot's changed since then, so it's kinda nice when we find something that hasn't.
The fact that couple is still arguing almost fills me with...I dunno. Hope, I guess.
If you ask me, that particular couple could benefit from a little change...
Pah! I cannot believe how many trips we have made simply to track down a single man!
It's all right to do this kind of thing every now and then.
I only pray this is not the calm before some manner of storm...
Say there, lad. Have you ever penned a missive?
You mean a letter? No. I'm not big on writing. It always takes me forever to figure out what I want to say.
What's to "figure out"? One simply takes quill in hand and unleashes their soul upon the canvas of the page!
Whatever you say, Weiss.
A shipwreck, is it? I suppose we might as well investigate, seeing as how we lack any other tenable leads.
Right. Let's head for the inlet.
Kainé? Emil?
We're gonna need to figure out some way to get inside that thing.
This ship is in a state of wanton decay. Surely we can find a hole or some such if we put our minds to it.
This place is pretty gloomy; I'm having a hard time imagining any townsfolk hanging around here.
Well, as we've no other leads...let the search begin!
Lotta cookware in here. I'm guessing this was the kitchen.
That would explain why it reeks of oil.
What the heck was THIS room for?
Ooo, look at the boxes! Let's peek inside.
That's food. Rotten food. ...<FONT=ITALIC>Very</FONT> rotten food.
Guess this was where they stored their food.
Gosh...the heck...for...
Look at...boxes! ...peek...
Food...rotten...
I guess...storeroom where...
...eck...room...
...all these...peek...
...otten...Very...
...this...stored...
Kya ha ha! Oh man, that smell is gettin' <FONT=ITALIC>ripe</FONT>!
How ya feelin' there, Sunshine?
Not great. Can't you tell?
Wait, so these corpses are...the people from town?
Yes, and they have been devoured. What a horrid fate.
Kya ha ha! Oh, we're gettin' reeeal close to somethin' nasty, Sunshine.
Ugh!
Damn! The ship won't hold at this rate!
Don't stop, lad!
They will crush this entire ship in order to get at us!
Enough dawdling! The ship is going to collapse!
Kainé and Emil will be fine—we must make good our own escapes at once!
Do you wish to be buried alive? Hurry!
Shades! Dammit, they're in the way!
Oh, great, these things regenerate!?
Only cut through the ones in your path or we shall be here until doomsday!
It looks like we can get out through that hole up there!
Why isn't this Shade being hurt by the sun!?
That is not precisely the case.
It most certainly IS being burned by the sunlight...
However, its regenerative abilities far outpace whatever damage the light is able to inflict.
Then we'll just have to up our own attacks to match.
It didn't matter how many people I ate!
I was never satisfied!
Nobody ever helped me!
He's the only one who was ever kind to me!
He taught me what kindness is!
I...I will become human!
We'll...we'll speak the same language...
And we will stay together!
You're doing it for <FONT=ITALIC>him</FONT>? How sad! How precious!
Kyaaa ha ha ha!
I dunno where the singin' lessons came from, but I DO know it's sure as hell tryin' to eat us!
Don't stop now! Focus on the next one!
Now is our chance. Attack with all that you have!
This light... Something is coming! Get out of the way at once!
Aw, listen! It's singing! This thing actually thinks it's a PERSON! Kyaaa ha ha ha!
Aw, look at that... It just can't say goodbye to its little-girl form! Ain't that cute!?
It destroyed its own tentacle!
A trifling matter for this beast, to be certain.
Do not underestimate its regenerative ability! Make its end a decisive one!
To think it could recover from such a grievous wound...
Ordinary attacks aren't gonna do shit against this thing!
Is this thing turning its body into spears and SHOOTING them at us?
What kind of Shade attacks you with ITSELF!?
Keep your guard up! This is no average Shade!
The number of spears flying our way is increasing!
Yeah, I can see that! Dammit!
This isn't working! We can't hold out!
My word... If this continues...
Hey! The guy from before's collapsed on the beach!
That Shade's got some kinda hard-on for him—we should take him hostage!
Shut your yap! I'm not in the business of using my blades on people.
Fine then! I guess we'll all just sit around a campfire and sing songs until we get murdered!
Goddammit!
That spear is laced with powerful magic!
Get back! It's about to explode!
There's so much magical power...
There's so much magical power...
Flee the area covered in light!
Here it comes! Dodge!
You get it's weakness by now, yeah, Sunshine?
Well then, get to carvin' this bastard up before we're all dead!
I know, dammit! I KNOW!
The core of this thing is in the mouth—we need to get up there!
Are you serious!?
Um, but how are we supposed to do that?
Instead of wasting time running your mouths, how about you keep attacking the damn thing until it falls over!?
Grimoire Weiss has a plan! Arm for the beast's arm after it swings down!
This will rob its body of support and throw it off balance!
Now! Run up the arm!
Why does it look like a little girl...?
Mere tricks, lad! This beast is a Shade for true!
Why do you try to stop me!?
All I want is to be with him!
...Shit!
You doing it for <FONT=ITALIC>him</FONT>? How sad! How precious!
The Shade is getting back up!
It's concentrating tremendous magical energy into its head!
Attacking it may cause the power gathered there to discharge!
Stop...getting in my way!
Now's your chance! Run, lad!
Attack the part of her that looks like a girl!
The Shade's core is inside its mouth! Hurry!
Where are you going!? We must stop the beast here so the town is not destroyed!
It's coming from below! Do not stop!
Aim for its arm after it swings down! This will throw it off balance!
How can it withstand such an onslaught!?
I...I'm really scared, guys!
We will be in grave danger if it unleashes that attack. We must stop it!
We will be in grave danger if it unleashes that attack. We must stop it!
Okay, but how!?
I will...become...human...
I...will become human!
This is...quite bad indeed...
Urgh...
Agh...
I think...we're in trouble...
What the hell are you doing!? STOP 'EM ALREADY!
My body won't... Damn it! Fuck!
Stop! Don't hurt these people!
Don't you...want to look at the sea together...?
So you've been lying to me this whole time!?
But you told me to sing...
You... You're a monster!
I want...to be human. I want us...to be together.
We can NEVER be together! You DISGUST me!
It...stopped?
Do not miss this chance! Use magic to deal the finishing blow!
We've only the strength for one final blast.
Get close enough that we cannot miss our target!
I shall endeavor to gather magical energy.
It...stopped?
Focus on the source of its magic... Aim for the head!
This is our last chance. Do not miss, lad!
Now! Fire!
Hey, Kainé?
Yeah?
When you were threatening that Shade on the beach the other day—
How did you know it was trying to protect the postman?
Just a feeling, I guess.
Huh. All right.
That poor woman... Losing her husband like that...
Where did you go, Mommy...?
Even if we can't catch fish, just being alive is a godsend...
A buncha townspeople disappeared along with that massive shipwreck...
God, but I miss those amazing fights they used to have.
What's going to happen to our town?
I wonder if there's anything I can do to help the town...
Even without those we have lost, the world relentlessly continues to turn...
I killed so many Shades when I was trying to rescue Yonah.
But now, I have this strange feeling like...
Like somehow they're not all bad.
...Couldn't for the life of me explain why, though.
Die, damn you! Die!
Hey! Get back! It's dangerous here!
Heh. I think that's my line, buddy.
Suppose I shouldn't just leave that guy to die.
What's a villager doing in a place like this?
Guess I might as well ask.
The hell are machines doing here?
And where are the villagers?
More of 'em? Goddammit...
Oh come on, MORE?!
No, I need to make sure every one of those things is smashed to bits.
Somebody wanna explain what robots are doing in there?
The hell are robots doing in the Forest of Myth?
I better make sure to wreck 'em all—there could be more in there.
The hell's goin' on here?
What's a place like this doing inside a tree?
Welcome to the sea of humanity.
Welcome to the cemetery of sin and punishment.
...The hell?
You...are a Replicant.
A manufactured existence.
Individual name: Kainé.
Who are you? Show yourselves!
Remain calm.
Do not be hasty.
Soon we shall meet.
Creepy little freaks...
This is an integrated information-management database designed to resemble a perennial plant.
It transmits phenomena recorded in its memory unit.
I don't understand a damn thing you're saying.
Observations of you have been recorded as well.
You...brought an end to Project Gestalt.
You killed the Original Gestalt. Now the remaining Gestalts run wild because they have nowhere left to go.
Your actions have caused the deaths of countless Replicants.
Show your damn faces already!
Do not be hasty. Soon we shall meet.
Soon we shall meet.
My name is k?K?∑?XH
My name is p!P!H?cs!
WHAT the hell are you saying!?
We are the administrators.
The administrators of this forest.
What the sweet crap is up with these freaks?
How truly fascinating you are.
You are just as we expected.
Come this way.
They are copies of you, shaped by machinery.
A collection of microscopic, plant-based propulsion units bound together with Maso particles.
The same as this very forest.
A massive forest of memories coalesced by the triumphs of quantum mechanics and Maso research.
A forest that records anything and everything about the world.
If you wanted me to follow any of this, you're gonna be real fuckin' disappointed!
Your comprehension is unnecessary.
After all, all you care for is killing. Is this not so?
These other mes are brittle as hell... I oughta be insulted!
It matters not how many copies you destroy.
They will simply disperse and immediately reconstruct themselves.
There is still much fun to be had.
We have finally come to an end.
God DAMN you're annoying!
I'm gonna tear these freaks apart, eat the pieces, and shit 'em into a trash can!
Fuuucking hell...
Have we reached the end?
Have you reached your limit?
Dammit!
How unfortunate.
I sense tremendous power in that magic circle. I think it's acting as an energy source.
If we can destroy it, all the other Kainés should disappear, too!
Got it!
Number 7: A magical weapon forged by humans.
A being who absorbed the power of Number 6 and transcended humanity.
Ummm, who is that? What are those voices?
Just a coupla little fucks.
I can't leave Emil behind!
I'll take care of the magic circle—you focus on kicking some Kainé butt!
Er, I mean, the other Kainés' butts. Not YOUR Kainé butt. YOU, the real Kainé—
Yeah, I get it, Emil! Just focus!
Gosh, it feels like it's been forever since we fought together!
This...seems familiar...
I think there was...someone else who used to fight with us...
My memories are...
Unusual phenomena-fluctuation observed.
Singularity signature detected in Replicant Kainé.
Fascinating.
Terribly fascinating.
Are you all right, Kainé!?
...Yeah.
Kainé! I did it!
Is that...a doorway?
Beyond here lies that which was lost.
The final hope—for you to reclaim.
There's no going back now.
Let's end this. ...All of it.
Kainé, I...
I feel like I've forgotten something really important...
Tell me about it.
You too?
Yeah. I can't really describe it, but it's like my mind is filled with this weird fog.
I think I...made a promise to somebody?
Like...that we would go eat something delicious?
Heh heh.
Well then, we'll just have to get those memories back.
Yeah!
I feel an enormous magical power ahead.
Just don't do anything rash. Got it?
Got it. Same goes for you, Kainé!
I don't want to be alone anymore.
...Yeah.
Oh my gosh... The magical energy is incredible!
That's gotta be what's powering these machines!
Okay, I'll destroy it. You handle the machines!
That is the core frame of this forest, within which a great variety of information is stored.
Inside it exists all that this world is, including the memories you have lost.
Though rather than memories, it might be best to say the "world" you have lost.
In any case, it is surely the answer you ought to seek.
Would you two shitsacks PLEASE shut up?!
She's a life! She has meaning and worth, and we're going to save her!
Everyone has something to live for. Even Kainé.<LF>...Even Yonah.
You don't get to decide who lives and who dies!
That voice... It's the one from my dreams.
I've heard that voice before...
These are your memories.
A record you repeatedly rewrote.
I'm who I am today because of you!
I'm not going to give up on you...
We made it this far because you were with us, Kainé!
Dammit... What IS this!?
Do you suffer?
Are you pained?
SHUT THE FUCK UUUP!
Where...am I?
Emil?
These are your memories.
These are your records.
This is your world.
Shades!?
Shades: Human souls that have gone Gestalt.
These Shades are but data reproduced via your records.
They are the true humans you slaughtered on your journey.
What the hell is this?
Sweet memories from deep within.
Bitter memories that were sealed away.
Beepy, wait! That's enough!
No! I can't live without you!
I don't wanna be alone again!
Goddammit, enough with this bullshit already!
You have heard many voices.
Fear. Hate. Rage. Suffering.
Each of them has meaning.
We are incomplete. But our friends make us whole!
We are mocked, abused, and hated. But our friends keep us strong!
That is what keeps us going!
Do not stand in the way of our lives!
Stop it, stop it, STOP IT!
I kill Shades! That's all there is to it!
You are a foreign entity in this world.
An error created by a discrepancy between memory and record.
I have not understood a SINGLE FUCKING THING you shitty little assgrabbers have said since we STARTED this goddamn adventure!
Get out, half-breed!
You disgust me! You disgust us all!
We don't want you!
Just leave us in peace!
Enough already!
Please, just SHUT UP!
You brought these Shades here!
Enough already!
Don't you dare call yourself human!
Get out!
We don't want you!
Get out of our village!
...Tch.
Shut your goddamn mouths already!
Fuck! I can't reach it!
Get your ugly ass down here!
I said, get DOWN here!
Wait, it disappeared!?
Uh oh. I think it's charging up its magic...
Get the fuck DOWN HERE you worthless piss-guzzling shit-rag!
I presume you know how to use magic, yes? Then give us a show, hussy!
I don't need your help to take out this goddamn fuck-waffle!
Right!
Hey, Weiss.
Yes?
...Thanks.
Have you been in your cups again?
Fuck your face.
Ah. That's more like it!
Now is our chance!
What impertinence! Skewer the accursed thing!
Use my power to knock the creature down with magic!
Do not relent in your assault!
Time to close this out!
Its attacks grow ever more fierce. Remain vigilant!
Like I care! I'm gonna fuck this thing up!
Shit, this thing is tough...
Let the next onslaught be our last!
What are you doing? You must use magic to stop this foe!
I know, goddammit!
It's going to charge! Strike it right in its ugly maw!
It's going to charge! Stop it with magic!
(Boy Nier normal drowning voice)
(Young adult Nier normal drowning voice)
Mmm. Are you all right, lad?
Yeah, I'm okay.
You have lost health. You must be more careful.
I hate to ask, but...can you not swim?
...Don't tell Yonah, okay?
If you cannot swim, why do you keep leaping into bodies of water!?
I-it's not me. It's almost like...my body just...does it on its own.
Everything in working order?
Yeah. Yeah, Weiss. I'm good.
Your health has diminished. Do be more careful next time, mmm?
I must say, I'm rather surprised you didn't bother to learn how to swim these past five years.
I can swim! My, uh...weapon is just heavy.
Whatever you say, lad.
Hey, Weiss?
Yes, lad?
Is there a way to swim using magic, or...?
No.
Figures.
Spth! Blth! Blech! I'm covered in sand.
Take care before all your health is lost.
Man, I HATE being covered in sand!
Spth! Blth! Yes, do try harder not to fall in, would you?
The space between my pages feels...crunchy.
I'd give anything to jump into some water right about now.
Despite your inability to swim? Are you mad!?
It was a joke, Weiss. Sheesh.
Tpphbbht... Well, great. I'm covered in sand.
Diving in sand is an excellent way to lose health. Do try to be more careful, mmm?
God, having sand in your clothes is the WORST.
It makes one want to enjoy a bath, for certain.
Weiss, can you even TAKE baths?
Yes.
...Huh. Okay then.
Perhaps humans are simply not designed to swim in sand.
Agreed.
And in that case, you might consider being a tad more careful?
...Agreed.
Dammit...
Where did that girl get to?
Doubtless she will make another sudden appearance at some point...
Say there...
Can you not hear me?
Why are you standing about like a slack-jawed ninny?
Sorry. Felt like I was...dreaming or something.
Sleeping on one's feet is quite the talent indeed.
Come now, there's the door.
Right... Let's go.
Would it not be wise to explore the rooms on the floor above us?
Let us investigate further in.
We've done enough searching here. Onward!
This little lantern has brought us quite far, hasn't it!
Yeah. And the light it gives off makes me feel... I dunno. Safe, somehow.
Well, aren't we the romantic!
Should we not be heading farther in?
Have you still not found the lantern? We've no alternative but to scour the ground for it.
You would return there? I'd rather not.
Is now truly the time to turn tail?
This sound... Is it a Shade?
What is with this ship, anyway?
There may be clues somewhere that tell of how it ran aground.
You would go back from whence we came?
There don't seem to be any Shades around, at least.
Fortunate for us. Now let no more time be wasted in our search for the townsfolk!
A kitchen, is it?
Ah, there is a passage this way as well.
A hidden room! How delightful.
A red jewel, is it?
The strange-thing store might deal in such articles.
Let's go check it out.
Huzzah to us for acquiring a red jewel, but is it truly all right to make a present of something we received at no cost?
I think it's the thought that counts here.
And whose thoughtfulness are we speaking of? Might I remind you the giver of this present is <FONT=ITALIC>not even here</FONT>.
What a journey this has been! Let us make for the couple's home at once.
I have to sing...and cheer myself up...
Where...did he...go?
Why...do I...feel this way?
I say, each time we encounter that bickering couple anew, we are made to endure an even further torrent of meaningless and incessant chatter!
Yeah, they love to talk, all right. Remind you of anyone?
Grimoire Weiss is one hundred times their better! You don't see this old tome flitting about starting donnybrooks and set-tos, now do you!?
Let's head for bag dude's house so we can give him his jewel.
I imagine it would be quickest to make for Seafront by way of the canal.
To think the creature's body could envelop such a massive ship...
This thing will destroy the town if we don't stop it.
It maintains a distance your blade cannot reach. Meet it with magic!
That thing ain't normal—so stay smart unless you wanna get dead!
Such a terrifying array of projectiles... Dodge as best you can!
I can't believe such a huge Shade even exists...
The head is immune to magic!
Aim for the tentacles with faces on them!
Tentacles with faces... How very ghastly!
I can't believe that little girl was actually THIS thing!
This monstrosity is unlike anything we've faced before. Remain vigilant!
This thing is gonna pay for what it did to those people!
The town will be in grave danger should we leave this creature be. We must end it here and now!
Weiss...!
I have to...get to Weiss...
Weiss... You okay?
O-of course...
Er, I mean, of course! Who do you think I am!? Such an attack is naught compared to the might of—
Weiss, shut up—there's something weird about the Shade right now.
Indeed? Well then, this might be our chance.
Even so, we likely only have magic enough for one final strike.
The parts that look human are immune to magic!
C'mere, you annoying little bastards.
I'll crush every last one of you!
It's been so quiet lately.
I feel like things used to be a lot more...lively.
Not sure WHY I feel that way, though.
Hey. Anybody home?
What are those things doing here?
Wait, did they kill the villagers!?
Oh come on, MORE?!
Ugh, they just keep on coming...
We have long been watching.
We have long been listening.
The stories of recycled vessels.
The voice of a recycled world.
What will you show us?
Will you show us your potential?
Entertain us.
What the heck? These robots seem different from the ones before.
Not different enough for me not to kill 'em.
Is this...the Shadowlord's castle?
Kainé, I'm sensing some powerful magic up ahead...
This is a very special place.
To you—and to the world.
It must be what's powering the robots... Let's smash the hell out of it!
We upgraded the data that was recreated from your memories.
Can you defeat this nightmare?
Shut your goddamn traps for one goddamn second and lemme kill it already!
Your efforts are futile. It cannot be stopped.
There is no escaping this nightmare.
Someone else was there when I first fought this bastard...
FUUUCK! Why can't I REMEMBER!?
Ugh, come ON already you fucking coward!
Okay... That hurt...
The situation is dangerous. Aim for where it's gathering magical energy!
Well done! Now clobber the beast!
Let's fuck it up good!
Blast! We were too slow.
Are you sound of mind, hussy? What you are attempting is extremely—
Cram it, book. I'm doing this.
I see...
Let us finish this!
Fucking hell, how is this thing STILL NOT DEAD!?
Do not falter! We attack again!
I have not understood a SINGLE FUCKING THING you shitty little ass-bangers have said since we STARTED this goddamn adventure!
Feels like there's a lot of Shades around lately...
Maybe I should check in on Yonah's village.
Its swing is powerful, but slow to recover! Dodge it and counterattack!
I think it's working!
It's sink or swim now, lad! Focus your attacks on the head!
Okay, now we've for SURE got it!
Not yet! The wound wasn't fatal!
Use its body as a foothold to climb up and attack the core in its mouth!
I think you can climb its tentacles!
Try using the Shade as a foothold!
Watch your step, lad! Do not tumble into the sea!
Why can't my sword cut these bullets?
Man, what a pain in my ass...
Shit. My attacks aren't working!
Ugh, how am I supposed to kill this asshat!?
Fuck... This is bad...
Use my magic to topple the beast.
I presume you know how to use magic, yes? Then give us a show, hussy!
I don't need your help to take out this goddamn fuck-waffle!
Your blade's attacks are useless.
Tch!
This is some twisted shit right here, and you're gonna pay!
I won't lose to you!
Your attacks may work now! Take your blade to it!
Let not your resolution waver before mere illusions again, hussy!
Don't worry! I'll do what needs to be done.
Why would robots be coming out of a place like that?
Yeaaah, this thing's planning something...
Get DOWN here, fucknuts!
...Quit it.
...Back off.
Whoa. What <FONT=ITALIC>is</FONT> this place?
At least there don't seem to be any bad guys around.
Emil, I didn't get a chance to ask yet with all the fighting and shit, but...
What happened to you back then? And where have you been? ...And why the hell do you have <FONT=ITALIC>four arms</FONT>?
K-Kainé, I...
Look, it's gonna take way too long to get into all that now.
Fine.
I was worried, you know?
Aw, Kainé...
But look at us now. Team Kamil, back together again!
Yeah, I guess so.
Stop distracting me.
You're an annoying fucker, aren't you?
You think you're funny, huh?
The hell are you looking at?
You catch a glimpse?
Enough already.
You think you're hot shit, huh?
This is your last warning.
All right, fuck off and die, you pervy little shit!
Hm? Is that...?
Hey! Over here!
